        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 7:28PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 727 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 3 miles northwest
of Dawson, or 46 miles east of Bismarck, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tappen, Dawson, Lake Isabel, and Crystal Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
